    public class Employee
extends java.lang.Object

        Constructor initializing the fields of the employee.
        Parameters:
        id - The identification number of the employee.
        phone - The phone number of the employee.
        division - The division number of the employee.
        years - How many years the employee has worked at the company.
        person - The personal information of the employee, this includes their first and last name, and their martial status.
        department - The department that the employee works at.

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
        Equals method compares this employee object with another to determine if they are equal. They are considered equal if all of the fields are equivalent, except the department field. This is because the same person can be in multiple departments at one time.
